The President has announced two new nominees for U.S. Attorneys and one new nominee for U.S. Marshal. These officials will play a crucial role in upholding the rule of law and enforcing federal law. The nominees were chosen for their dedication to law enforcement, professionalism, experience, commitment to equal justice, and support for the independence of the Department of Justice. The President has also proposed a budget that includes increased funding for law enforcement to address the rising crime rate. Additionally, efforts are being made to combat gun crime by increasing police presence, supporting community prevention programs, and cracking down on illegal gun trafficking. So far, the President has announced 65 nominees for U.S. Attorneys and 21 nominees for U.S. Marshals. The article provides information about the backgrounds and qualifications of the three nominees mentioned. Peter D. Leary is a candidate for the United States Attorney for the Middle District of Georgia, Jill E. Steinberg is a candidate for the United States Attorney for the Southern District of Georgia, and Craig J. Anderson is a candidate for the United States Marshal for the District of Montana.